Identifying the need for, creating, and overseeing the delivery of common enterprise components that improve the delivery and maintainability of data products.
Defining solutions that span multiple technologies, including SAS, Hadoop & Big Data, Azure, Teradata Data Warehouse, ETL tools (e.g., Informatica), and BI tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI).
Collaborating with Credit Risk Business Stakeholder, Service Owners, Tech Leads and Line of Business (LOB) Leads to prioritize, size, and assess the requirements and backlog.
Ensuring projects and programs align with design principles and standards.
Working with business units to understand credit risk-related data elements, including reference data, metadata, and data lineage.
Guiding Agile teams in designing, developing, testing, implementing, and supporting technical solutions using full-stack development tools, technologies, and DevOps processes.

Required Skills:
5+ years of experience in a large and complex Credit Risk and/or Banking environment.
10+ years of experience within projects and/or delivery of business and technology solutions, involving engineering of complex data processes.
5+ years of Advanced SQL and SAS experience particularly in data manipulation, cleansing using Base SAS, SAS/Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Consle and overall SAS Platform.
5+ years of experience in technologies such as Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase, Python, Java, Spring Boot, Git, Flink, CosmosDB, Akka, Scala, SQL, Synapse
Extensive experience in warehousing, modelling, integration tools such as Informatica, Sterling and be familiar with business intelligence tools such as IBM Cognos/TM1, Power Bi, Tableau.
Experience designing for cloud platforms, including serverless architecture, preferably Azure.


What's on offer?
This contract is available for an initial 6-month term with likely extension on a long term project. Located in Sydney or Melbourne, this role offers a hybrid working arrangement.

How to Apply:
Please upload your resume to apply. We will be in touch with further instructions for suitably skilled candidates. Please note that you will be required to complete selection criteria to complete your application for this role.

Call Katrina Gabriel on 0489 923 756 or email katrinag@whizdom.com.au for any further information.

Candidates will need to be willing to undergo pre-employment screening checks which may include, ID and work rights, security clearance verification and any other client requested checks.

